rComments: Great professor, cares about his students and he is very fair. One of the best eng profs at uOttawa for sure.

Prof.Ahmed was good,returning emails fast,doing his best for his students to succeed but lectures were monotone and grading was taking long time.Given that this is a project based course,the workload is quite heavy with multiple assignments, quizzes and term project but exams were pretty straightforward and not weighted much.Great choice!

Took machine design and also this course from him. In general, even though his lectures are very monotone and confusing and the course tends to get difficult from time to time, practise problems and past exams are the key elements to pass this course with a good grade and he returns emails quite fast. Exams are pretty straightforward. Good choice!
Amazing Prof. Goes out of his way to help students, a genuine guy. Would recommend to anyone, 10/10.

Awful teaching. He's extremely lazy and covers very little material during his lectures which are very slow. The exams this semester were quite difficult, especially when considering how poorly he delivers the material, so beware.
Caring prof, makes things very clear and wants you to succeed. Genuinely has a passion for what he teaches and knows his concepts really well. will be taking him again

Great person and prof. always there for you, responds to emails anytime any day. teaches well and cares about his students and wants you to succeed. would suggest him for any class in the future too, seriously a great prof. ignore the bad reviews, this guy is one of the best I've had. HIGHLY recommended.
This man may be nice, but he can't teach. His notes are awful, they skip all over the place, are illegible in others, and don't provide a comprehensive explanation of the course material.
Ive had several classes with him. He gives clear criteria and tries to help wherever he can. His lecture notes are a little unstructured so not all concepts are conveyed super well.

Mumbles a lot. Takes a lot of time to explain the theory behind some concepts while skimming through problems. The textbook was used but older versions (with the same problems) can be found online, there's no need to actually buy the textbook.
Excellent Professor.

Lectures were dry at first until many students emailed Ahmed asking for examples to be done. Lectures improved from here on out. Tests you exactly what is taught in class. Weekly quizzes are also straight from the assigned problems
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Caring', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Mechanics 2 is one of the most difficult MCG course that I have taken so far and Prof. Ahsan did a great job in teaching. He used Power Point Slides + Board notes and solved many problems in the class too to get his point across. He is always available and super helpful .

Nice guy but his notes are horribly vague with 0 structure, and good luck learning from the tb because it is DENSE. For the weekly DGD our TA just copies the solutions for ONE question on the board, the rest is "individual work" and a quiz. You'll need to learn everything solo. Go home and do the tutorial qs/suggested problems.
Awesome Professor. Very helpful. Posts online notes and recommended problems.

Horrible note taking. Very slow, all over the place, almost impossible to pay attention to this monotone man drone on. I guess someone in his past course must have told him to "be more clear" because he stops to explain the simplest things, like the angle between a horizontal and vertical line is 90 degrees, or explain what the Cartesian system is
Good
Great prof. Great notes. Straight forward exams. Practice the questions he solves in class and similar questions and you'll pass for sure. Practice DGDs and put a bit more effort and you'll get an A.
He's a very caring prof, he will help in whatever manner he can. Only problem is that his notes lack structure and order thus it's difficult to understand what he's teaching.

A very few profs care about their students and Ahsan Ahmed is one of them who cares about the students. His lectures are not very fluent, but having him as a prof is  relief because he will let you know what the course is about and how you need to study for it.
Dawg... you better sit in front if you wanna see his writing

One of the best profs you'll have in MCG undergrad. A lot courses can be tough, but any class with Ahsan is a relief, as you know there's very little tricks.   He teaches what he'll test you on, and more often than not, he'll tell you what specific problems you need to know.  He's not the greatest teacher, but he's one of the best.

There is a lot of material in this class. Midterm didn't go over great but it wasn't worth a lot. The project is worth major marks, get a good group and follow the grading criteria. Textbook is expensive and not great - find the Shigley one he uses. Final was pretty fair - was similar to questions he did in class and assigned / DGD problems.

Note: taken during summer. Prof works through a lot of problems in class that always reflect the midterms / exams. His expectations are pretty clear and is fair when it comes to marking. Work through the in class / assigned problems and you are guaranteed to pass. Weekly quizzes are very good for catching up. Class is mostly equations.

man I have no idea what everyone here is talking about. nothing about this class is clear. midterm is NOTHING like assignments or content discussed in his class. he's a nice guy for sure but that only goes so far. when the material is this difficult it would be nice to have a prof who could teach.

Ahmed is a meticulous, fair and knowledgeable professor who knows his stuff very well. Always available to students whether in person or via email. Took   few courses with him and all went really well. Clear grading criteria.  I recommend taking courses with him.
He's a great guy
Took a few courses with him, one of the only profs you know has your back. Well respected by most students because he tests what he teaches and vice versa.

Theory is hard to follow as he just repeats the textbook however his explanations and diagrams aren't very clear. He gives clear examples however these are just from the solution manual so you can simply study off the textbook. Tests accurately reflect homework problems.

Ahmed is amazing. His lectures can be quite boring and he sometimes gets a little flustered but he knows his stuff. He posts a ton of practise problems for you to work on. Do those and you'll get an A in the class. No need for the textbook. Super helpful and friendly dude outside of class too.

Good prof, cares about his students. Wants them to succeed. If you genuinely do the work, and solve the assigned problems - you will pass no problem. Profs expectations for the final were clear. Saving studying for the day before the final may be harder as it takes some practice to learn how to solve the problems.
Sometimes tough to understand due to his accent and the chaos of his notes and the way he writes on the board but he's an easy grader.
Summer 3145 is nice and simple with him, no surprises, no wasting time, fundamentals are taught and tested.
took a few mech eng courses with him, he's faculty of education so he makes a proper effort to teach. Difficulty is on the easy side as long as you put in effort.

Brilliant prof. Very helpful, extremely nice and approachable, and always willing to help his students if you go to him. Quizzes and midterm strongly reflect (exactly are) what is covered in the lecture. If he sees you putting in the effort, he will recognize it, and he also remembers faces. Highly recommend to take a class w him if possible.
Awesome Instructor, very helpful, explains everything in detail. Quizzes and Exam reflects the stuff covered in the class. Always eager to assist students. Recommend taking course with this prof.

Really hard to follow in class. Ignores a lot of questions. To him, everything is crucial to the course.  He over explains simple things like 3d, and quickly covers more difficult subjects.  He also told a student to leave for asking another student about something in class, because he was "disturbing the entire class".

There are profs who will try to put you down, some that don't care and others that are clueless of the material they are teaching. This guy is the exact opposite, helpful, encouraging and straigh to the point. Uses textbook and writes detailed notes on the board. I recommend his course, signed up just to rait him.
Really good prof! He made such a hard course very easy to understand. His exams are very easy as well and he doesn't like to fail anyone
Good prof. The midterm and final were not that hard even though the material covered in class wasn't that easy. Just make sure you attend every class and you'll do great in this course.
Had him in first year and then again in third year; his teaching has greatly improved and you can tell he really cares about his students. Good sense of humour and eager to help.

He is to the point and tells you all the material you need to know for tests directly. Just show up to class, do the assigned problems. The exam questions and quiz questions are taken from the book and sometimes the exact same. I recommend taking this teacher

He is a very good prof, takes a lot of time to explain everything thoroughly and will always repeat if you don't understand. He may sometimes seem strict but he's a nice guy. Don't talk in class, and attend the lecture and you will do fine.
Hard to understand, boring.  Do not talk in his class, or he'll take off marks
To the point professor. Go to the class do the assigned problems and you will get a good professor. I recommend taking the course with him.
Good Teacher if you Read the texbook before attending class you will understand . He will simplify the textbook content so you have to know what he's talking about . He is open to feedback
Terrible
